# Variant Sifter visualizers

When adding a new visualizer or track to KP Variant Sifter, **create a new component** instead of modifying existing portal components or shared research visualizers.

## Do

- Add a new `VariantSifter*.vue` component under `kpVariantSifter/`
- Extract canvas/render logic into a sibling `variantSifter*.js` module when non-trivial
- Wire the new visualizer in `variantSifterSections.js` and parent layout (`VariantSifterCanvas.vue`, `VariantSifterAssociationsPlot.vue`, etc.)
- Reuse shared VS utilities: `variantSifterPlotShared.js`, `variantSifterRegionZoom.js`, `VARIANT_SIFTER_PLOT_MARGIN`
- Accept `sharedCanvasWidth` from the plot stack so x-axis alignment stays correct
- Accept `plotMarkers` (`starredVariants`, `positionMarkers`) and call `renderPlotMarkerLines()` from `variantSifterPlotMarkers.js` after the main draw so stars and position pins align across tracks
- Clamp dot menus and tooltips inside their plot container via `variantSifterPopupPosition.js` so popups never render under drawer tabs or off-screen

## Do not

- Modify `ResearchGenesTrack.vue`, `ResearchRegionPlot.vue`, or other legacy `researchPortal/` visualizers for VS features
- Add VS-specific props or layout hacks to shared portal components
- Fork behavior inside an existing VS visualizer when the feature is a distinct track/section — give it its own component
- Add decorative borders around sections, tracks, or plots unless structurally required (e.g. drawer chrome, floating menus, modal frames). Canvas plots and drawer content areas should be borderless by default.

## Examples

```text
# Good
kpVariantSifter/VariantSifterCredibleSetsTrack.vue
kpVariantSifter/variantSifterCredibleSetsRender.js

# Avoid
Editing ResearchCredibleSets.vue to add VS behavior
Adding VS-only props to VariantSifterAssociationRegionPlot.vue for a new section
```

## Reference pattern

Follow `VariantSifterGenesTrack.vue` + `variantSifterGenesTrackRender.js`: thin Vue shell, pure render module, parent-owned data fetching, shared plot stack width.
